 hem. This event is described in the following form:\n\nT t\n\nHere t is
  the time the table became available (again\, in minutes past opening time
 )\,\n\n \n\n* Quit: This is a sentinel event indicating the end of the i
 nput file. It has the following form:\n\nQ\n\nWhen the events in the file 
 have been processed\, compute and print the average waiting time per custo
 mer. If there are still people waiting for tables\, print a summary of who
  is still waiting.\n\n \n\nSample Data File:\n\nHere is a sample data fil
